```

The issue is likely that when `extraInterfaces()` is called after `serializable()` or vice versa, there might be a conflict in how the interfaces are stored. Looking at the `extraInterfaces` method in `MockSettingsImpl.java`, it simply replaces the `extraInterfaces` array with the new values:

```java
public MockSettings extraInterfaces(Class<?>... extraInterfaces) {
    // validation code...
    this.extraInterfaces = extraInterfaces;  // This replaces ALL interfaces!
    return this;
}
```

Ah! That's the bug! When `extraInterfaces()` is called, it completely replaces the array, so if `serializable()` was called previously (which adds `Serializable.class` to the array), that interface gets lost when `extraInterfaces(List.class)` is called afterwards.

